      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING MEHARY (1) filled a minor placing last start at Q Straight behind Special Rocky (19.20) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Sure to be about the mark. SMOKY CHIPOTLE (2) was strong over this course and distance last time despite filling the minors, finishing 4.5 lengths behind Zipping Daytona in 19.91 and recording a new PB here. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. I'M THE PROBLEM (8) scored by 1.5 lengths last time (16.71) in a Grade 5 over 300m at Q Straight. Already a winner from this draw. Can feature in the finish. ZIPPING NARWHAL (4) warrants respect with the drop in distance.",
